<TITLE> DU hall suspends 8 over BCL clash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 25 (bdnews24.com)--Dhaka University's Poet Jashim Uddin Hall authorities on Tuesday suspended studies eight students linked to Bangladesh Chhtra League following a factional clash on Monday midnight that left at least 12 students injured. They students were suspended for their involvement with the clash and residing in the hall without approval. The authorities also warned the hall unit's BCL president Mohammad Abdur Rahman and general secretary Enayet Quazi over allegations that they clashed with their followers to control the hall, the provost said. Rahman is a MA student of Islamic history and culture, and Quazi, a fourth-year student of political science. Dr Akhtaruzzaman told bdnews24.com that they had been asked to immediately submit the names of the unruly students to the hall authorities Whoever would cause disturbance in the hall would face administrative action, he also said. Those punished were Mostafa Amin, a third-year underraduate student of dramatics, Mohammad Mehedi Hasan, a second-year student of international relations, Mehedi Hasan, a second-year student of linguistics, Liton Mahmud, a fourth-year student of Islamic history and culture, Emanul Haque, a second-year student of mass communication and journalism, Abdullah Al Masum, a second-year student of tourism, 'Jahid' and 'Bappi', students of dramatics. b
